          </div>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <!-- Main Content: The Core Article -->
      <article class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p
          id="introduction"
          class="text-2xl leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant font-medium first-letter:text-8xl first-letter:font-black first-letter:text-primary first-letter:mr-4 first-letter:float-left first-letter:leading-none mb-16"
        >
          Distributed consensus is the fundamental problem of reaching an
          agreement among a group of independent processes on a single data
          value or a course of action. In modern architecture, this is the
          bedrock of reliability.
        </p>
        <h2
          id="paxos-paradox"
          class="font-headline font-black text-4xl text-on-surface tracking-tighter mt-24 mb-10 border-b border-outline-variant/10 pb-4"
        >
          The Paxos Paradox
        </h2>
        <p class="mb-10 text-on-surface-variant/90 leading-relaxed text-lg">
          While Raft has become the industry favorite for its relative
          simplicity and understandability, Paxos remains the mathematical
          titan. The difficulty isn't in the logic itself, but in the edge cases
          that occur during network partitions. Consider a three-node cluster
          attempting to elect a leader during a transient failure.
        </p>
        <!-- Code Block Component -->
        <div
          id="implementation-in-go"
          class="my-16 bg-surface-container-lowest rounded-lg overflow-hidden border border-outline-variant/20 shadow-2xl"
        >
          <div
            class="flex items-center justify-between px-6 py-4 bg-surface-container-high/50 border-b border-outline-variant/20"
          >
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <div class="flex gap-1.5">
                <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-error/40"></div>
                <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-tertiary/40"></div>
                <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-primary/40"></div>
              </div>
              <span
                class="text-[10px] font-headline font-black uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-outline ml-2"
                >consensus.go</span
              >
            </div>
            <span
              class="text-outline text-[10px] font-black uppercase tracking-widest flex items-center gap-2"
            >
              <span aria-hidden="true" class="material-symbols-outlined text-base"
                >content_copy</span
              >
              Static Code Sample
            </span>
          </div>
          <div class="p-8 overflow-x-auto font-mono text-sm leading-relaxed">
            <pre
              class="text-slate-300"><code><span class="text-primary">func</span> (n *Node) <span class="text-tertiary">RequestVote</span>(args *VoteArgs, reply *VoteReply) &#123;
    n.mu.<span class="text-primary">Lock</span>()
    <span class="text-primary">defer</span> n.mu.<span class="text-primary">Unlock</span>()

    <span class="text-slate-500">// Check if the candidate's term is stale</span>
    <span class="text-primary">if</span> args.Term &lt; n.currentTerm &#123;
        reply.VoteGranted = <span class="text-tertiary">false</span>
        reply.Term = n.currentTerm
        <span class="text-primary">return</span>
&#125;

    <span class="text-slate-500">// Logical clock update and state transition</span>
    <span class="text-primary">if</span> args.Term &gt; n.currentTerm &#123;
        n.<span class="text-tertiary">becomeFollower</span>(args.Term)
&#125;
&#125;</code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="mb-10 text-on-surface-variant/90 leading-relaxed text-lg">
          The above snippet illustrates the critical term check. In a
          distributed environment, the notion of "time" is replaced by "terms"
          or "epochs". If a node receives a request with a lower term than its
          own, it must reject it to maintain the integrity of the linearizable
          history.
        </p>
        <div
          class="relative bg-surface-container-low border-l-[6px] border-primary p-12 my-20 overflow-hidden group"
        >
          <div
            class="absolute -right-4 -bottom-4 opacity-5 group-hover:opacity-10 transition-opacity"
          >
            <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-9xl">format_quote</span>
          </div>
          <blockquote
            class="text-2xl font-light italic text-on-surface leading-snug"
          >
            "Reliability in distributed systems is not about preventing failure,
            but about orchestrating the recovery from it without the user ever
            noticing."
          </blockquote>
        </div>
        <h3
          id="practical-trade-offs"
          class="font-headline font-black text-3xl text-on-surface mt-20 mb-8 tracking-tighter"
        >
          Practical Trade-offs
        </h3>
        <ul class="space-y-6 mb-20 list-none p-0">
          <li class="flex gap-6 items-start group">
            <span
              class="text-primary font-black font-headline text-xl leading-none"
              >01</span
            >
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h4 class="text-on-surface font-bold font-headline mb-2 text-lg">
                Latency vs. Consistency
              </h4>
              <p class="text-on-surface-variant text-base leading-relaxed">
                Every round of consensus adds a network hop, increasing the P99
                latency of your write operations.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-6 items-start group">
            <span
              class="text-primary font-black font-headline text-xl leading-none"
              >02</span
            >
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h4 class="text-on-surface font-bold font-headline mb-2 text-lg">
                Quorum Size
              </h4>
              <p class="text-on-surface-variant text-base leading-relaxed">
                Increasing the node count improves fault tolerance but makes the
                consensus phase significantly slower.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-6 items-start group">
            <span
              class="text-primary font-black font-headline text-xl leading-none"
              >03</span
            >
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h4 class="text-on-surface font-bold font-headline mb-2 text-lg">
                Storage Overhead
              </h4>
              <p class="text-on-surface-variant text-base leading-relaxed">
                Maintaining a multi-paxos log requires significant disk I/O and
                complex pruning strategies.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <hr class="border-outline-variant/10 my-24" />
